Heritrix uses java native logging directly.  It does not go via a 
commons-logging-like intermediary (Maybe it should if embedding Heritrix 
is a popular practise).  Because of this, I believe, you are out-of-luck 
and will need to set up individual configurations: one for the 
commons-logging+log4j that the hosting application seems to use and then 
config. for heritrix native logging.

You might consider writing code to read the log4j configuration mapping 
its configuration format into configuration of Heritirix&#39;s native 
logging since they are not too different and since you are embedding 
anyways.

Regards the exception in the below, try cleaning up the state 
directory.  Perhaps an unclean shutdown of your embedding application 
didn&#39;t give Heritrix shutdown code a chance to run.

St.Ack


